TEXT.P:
-- the mainland hopes to forge good ties with the current U.S.
administration, to be admitted to the World Trade Organization as
early as possible and to smoothly host the 2008 Olympic Games;

-- Build trust and confidence: Both sides should encourage
further exchanges within society and uphold the principles of parity
and mutual respect in the negotiation process;

-- Establish concrete mechanisms early in the peace process to
avoid deadlocks in negotiation: Both sides should find ways to keep
moving forward the cooperation to maintain dialogue;

The major points of the consensus, which the government has
promised to follow "to the letter" despite the non-binding nature of
the EDAC consensus, are as follows;

-- Amend within six months regulations that prohibit construction
on land suitable for construction or regulations that discourage land
owners from developing their land;

-- "Taiwan first," "global management," "mutual benefits," and
"risk control management" are the pivotal principles regarding trade
and commerce activities across the Taiwan Strait;

-- Adopt a "proactive openness and effective management" policy
to replace the previous "no haste, be patient" policy regarding
mainland-bound investment;

-- Set up flexible mechanisms to monitor movements of capital
between the two sides; and introduce mainland Chinese capital to the
local property and real estate market;
